    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Multicellular eukaryotic life forms characterized by photosynthesis, in which chemical energy is produced from water, minerals, and carbon dioxide with the aid of pigments and the radiant energy of the Sun. However, also included in the kingdom are plants that do not produce their food by photosynthesis, but rather are parasitic and live off of other living plants. Other plants are saprophytic, obtaining their food from dead organic matter. Plants have cells that contain cellulose in their walls and are therefore to some extent rigid. There is also an absence of organs of locomotion, resulting in a more or less stationary existence as well as no sensory and nervous systems. There are over 300,000 living species of plants.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000093795/Encyclopedia Britannica Online (2002-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000047487/Classification of Living Things (2005-2012)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000114707/Oxford English Dictionary Online (2002-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Levende structuren die deel uitmaken van het plantenrijk; doorgaans zijn ze niet in staat tot voortbeweging en bezitten ze geen specifiek gevoels- of denkorgaan of spijsverteringskanaal, en kunnen ze zich volledig in leven houden op anorganische stoffen.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052381/Van Dale Engels-Nederlands (1989)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>以行光合作用為特徵的多細胞真核生物，透過水、礦物質、二氧化碳以及色素和太陽輻射能的輔助而產生化學能量。然而，植物界中也包含不靠光合作用來製造養分的植物，而是以寄生與仰賴其他植物為生。其餘的則是腐生生物，從死亡生物的有機物質中獲得養分。植物細胞的細胞壁含有纖維素，因此在某種程度上是堅硬的。此外植物也缺乏活動器官，多為靜止不動，且沒有感覺與神經系統。現存有超過三十萬種的植物種類。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052784/TELDAP database (2009-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Formas de vida eucarióticas multicelulares caracterizadas pela fotossíntese, na qual a energia química é produzida a partir da água, minerais e dióxido de carbono com o auxílio de pigmentos e da energia radiante do sol. No entanto, também estão incluídas no reino as plantas que não produzem seus alimentos por fotossíntese, mas sim são parasitas e vivem de outras plantas vivas. Outras plantas são saprofíticas, obtendo seu alimento de matéria orgânica morta. As plantas possuem células que contêm celulose em suas paredes e, portanto, são até certo ponto rígidas. Há também uma ausência de órgãos de locomoção, resultando em uma existência mais ou menos estacionária, bem como na ausência de sistemas sensoriais e nervosos. Existem mais de 300.000 espécies vivas de plantas.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Portuguese</Note_Language>
